cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SY

This paper is about robot grasping, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a new approach that combines high-level reasoning (using probabilistic logic) and low-level learning (mapping visual features to grasping points) for task-dependent grasping. This involves using object/task ontologies and affordances, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach also involves learning from visual features, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the approach involves controlling a robot, which is a subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
